    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-12T13:59:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-12T13:59:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/6–1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MOOREBT1"
                            >Moore</persName>, cleared by <gloss target="#t_GER1">GER</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>,
                        and <persName corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1">MacArthur</persName>. Transmitted
                        by <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>. Repeated to London,
                        Bonn, and Geneva.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-12T14:59:00-04:00"
                            >June 12, 1954—2:59 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Edcol1">Edcol</gloss> 122. I have heard with interest
                        <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>’s report on
                    Ambassadors’ meeting in London,<note n="2" xml:id="d527fn2">On June 9–10,
                            <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> had chaired a
                        meeting of Chiefs of Mission, at London which included <persName
                            corresp="#p_ALDRICHWW1">Aldrich</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_CONANTJB1">Conant</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_DILLONCD1">Dillon</persName>, Deputy U.S. Representative to
                            <gloss target="#t_NAC1">NAC</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MARTINEM1">Edwin M. Martin</persName> and others.
                        Further documentation on the meeting is presented in <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v06p1">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> particularly recommendation proceed with message from
                    President to <persName corresp="#p_COTYR1">Coty</persName> and foreign
                    ministers’ meeting under Article 132 of <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>
                    treaty along lines my conversation with <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1"
                        >Spaak</persName> in Geneva (<gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 28
                    April 29).<note n="3" xml:id="d527fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_951">p. 951</ref>.</note> On
                    assumption fall of <persName corresp="#p_LANIELJ1">Laniel</persName>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d527fn4">On June 12, the <persName corresp="#p_LANIELJ1"
                            >Laniel</persName> government was defeated in debate over Indochina,
                        amidst charges that it had schemed for an American intervention there, by a
                        vote of 304–292. See editorial note, <ref target="#pg_972">p.
                        972</ref>.</note> will not result in new elections, I believe we should push
                    ahead promptly but quietly to develop this scenario. I suggest <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> let <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1"
                        >Spaak</persName> know of our approval in principle and <persName
                        corresp="#p_ALDRICHWW1">Aldrich</persName> should inform British, subject to
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName>’s determination timing of
                    these approaches. Believe <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName>
                    should bear in mind importance of getting British agreement in principle,
                    including, if possible, idea of message from <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1"
                        >Churchill</persName>, before <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1"
                        >Spaak</persName> gets too far out on limb.</p>
                <p>In meantime, we will urgently consider here best form of message from President
                    to <persName corresp="#p_COTYR1">Coty</persName>. For this purpose we need
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_DILLONCD1">Dillon</persName>’s comments on text of note given in
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 4131 May 18<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d527fn5">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_956">p. 956</ref>.</note>
                    which, modified to take form of Presidential message, seems more suitable for
                    present purpose than text in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 4408 June
                        4.<note n="6" xml:id="d527fn6">Not printed. (740.5/6–254)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Timing proposed conference of six difficult from point of view my schedule even
                    assuming meeting would last only one day or two at most. June 30–July 1 look
                    possible now but it would be virtually out <pb facs="1014" n="970"
                        xml:id="pg_970"/> of the question for me to accept an earlier date. Any
                    later feasible date would run toward middle July as I am now thinking in terms
                    Montevideo Conference opening July 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
